A 6-year-old boy in serious condition after he was hit by a stray bullet at a shopping centre in Centurion on Sunday.On arrival paramedics found the child in the back seat of a vehicle and noticed that he sustained a gunshot wound to his right shoulder. The boy was treated on the scene and rushed to a nearby hospital by ER24 for further care.ER24 Spokesperson Werner Vermaak said &#8220;Although the exact circumstances surrounding the incident is not yet known, it is understood that the child was sleeping in the car when an apparent shootout occurred nearby. Bystanders on the scene explained that the shooting incident occurred between security guards and robbers during an alleged robbery. One of the stray bullets went into the vehicle and into the child s shoulder&#8221;.At this stage, it is not clear if the child was left in the car unattended at the time when he sustained the injury. The exact cause of the incident is not yet known.By the time paramedics left the scene, police were not yet in attendance.-TNA Reporter 